==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trivalent
<hw>Triv"a*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + L. <ets>valens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. See
<er>Valence</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having a valence of
three; capable of being combined with, substituted for, or compared
with, three atoms of hydrogen; -- said of triad atoms or radicals; thus,
nitrogen is <xex>trivalent</xex> in ammonia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trivalve</ent>⟦br⟧
